    "summary": "My grandmother told stories, my father is a story teller, I love telling stories. The greatest among the greatest, heroes like Mahatma Ghandi and Martin Luther King, were story tellers. \nMy stories are tales about a rapidly changing world, a world that makes many anxious and angry. But in which, surprisingly, a lot remains the same. Stories about the tremendous progress we experience and the problems we resolve. \nI write my stories as a journalist, I publish them in books and I convey them in person during lectures and presentations.I describe myself as a Curious Cosmopolitan. 'Curious', as I am very inquisitive to broad global developments. 'Cosmopolitan', because I believe that people around the world bear responsibility for one another. \n'Be the change that you wish to see in the world', Ghandi told us. Martin Luther King added: 'Injustice anywhere is a threat to justice everywhere'.",
