                    "company": "thecuriouscosmopolitan.com",
                    "description": "How magnificent is \u2018I have a dream\u2019 of Martin Luther King? How moving was the speech that Michelle Obama delivered to support Hillary Clinton? Words can create something beautiful; words can move people into action \u2013 though I know very well that words can kill too.\nTeaching, lecturing and giving presentations is painting with words, although you have to charge these words with facial expressions, gestures and authenticity. I was a lecturer  at a journalism college for thirteen years. For nearly twenty years I have been a guest lecturer at several schools and universities. I still learn - from my own failures and from my students, who are getting smarter by the day.",
                    "title": "Lecturer and public speaker",
                    "employment_type": null
                },
                {
                    "location": "Tilburg Area, Netherlands",
                    "date": {
                        "start": {
                            "month": 1,
                            "day": null,
                            "year": 1998
                        },
                        "end": {
                            "month": null,
                            "day": null,
                            "year": null
                        }
                    },
                    "company": "thecuriouscosmopolitan.com",
                    "description": "I started writing in the early eighties, and I have been working as a professional journalist since 1998. I am based in Tilburg in the Netherlands, and Blantyre in Malawi. I have published articles in major newspapers and news magazines in the Netherlands and Belgium. Moreover, I had spoken columns and commentaries on the public radio. \nAlthough I have been a journalist for nearly thirty years, I currently feel that I am shifting away from mainstream journalism. When I started, I was mainly concerned with the publication itself. Did I correctly quote the people that I had interviewed? Did I apply the adversarial principle? Was my language accurate? \nRight now I am more and more concerned about the impact of my work on society. How do we, journalists, influence people and what is our responsibility?",
                    "title": "Journalist, Essayist & Author",
                    "employment_type": null
                },
